Fixes #93 

Includes minimal refactoring to easily switch between full testing as well as limited NCCoE testing

@christianpaquin : I had to implement this with hardcoded algorithms for your project now because you also wanted classical algs tested -- and unlike the PQ-algorithms, they cannot be selected by NIST strength. Please check the set is as you want it (`sigs_levels` and `kem_levels` are paired).

In general, the implementation has been done to quickly revert back to testing the full set of algorithms if we want to have this at the www.openquantumsafe.org/benchmarking site.

Also, I continue to be concerned about the "absolute" value of these "local handshake" numbers; their value may lie in "relative" comparability (between classic and PQ algs), though -- particularly in light of #97 (which may be an issue with OpenSSL3 in general or oqsprovider): My interest in solving such riddles is somewhat proportional to other's concern about it....

@dstebila If you approve and merge still today the first weekly run of this new set of algorithms should happen in the weekly run happening tonight if memory serves.
